body:
I attempted to pre-process data for my application with a build script, but I forgot to copy some `[dependencies]` to `[build-dependencies]` and got a very confusing E0432 when trying to build.


Given the following code: 

```rust
use walkdir::WalkDir;
use serde_json::json;

fn main() {
        for entry in WalkDir::new("crates").into_iter().filter_map(|e| e.ok()) {
[following has been omitted]}}
```

The current output is:

```
error[E0432]: unresolved import `walkdir`
 --> build.rs:1:5
  |
1 | use walkdir::WalkDir;
  |     ^^^^^^^ use of undeclared crate or module `walkdir
```
Ideally there should be a case for handling those few times where a "missing" dependency is spotted under different [ ] 

I know there won't be many cases like that, but I guess it would be helpful for those few scatterbrains like myself.
